content:
OUT! CAUGHT! Game, set and match! Ben Sears finishes with a five-fer and New Zealand win the game by 43 runs to clean sweep the ODI series 3-0! Sears smartly takes pace off this time and follows the batter making room, on a length, Sufiyan Muqeem is cramped up a bit and whips it off the upper half of the bat in an attempt to get it over the infield on the off side, but ends up hitting it straight to mid off. Muhammad Abbas moves to his left and takes a fine catch.
Sufiyan Muqeem c M Abbas b B Sears 2 (6b 0x4 0x6)
Short of a length, on off, Sufiyan Muqeem looks to hoick across but misses.
Short again, on leg, Sufiyan Muqeem looks to pull and gets a top edge that falls short of the keeper.

In the air, but falls safe. Seems like Tim Seifert lost it in the night sky. Back of a length, on middle, Akif Javed pulls it off the outer half of the bat to the left of deep square leg. Tim makes all the ground but the ball just drops down to his left. The batters take one.
Good length, angling in, on leg, Akif Javed has a wild swing but misses. The ball zips past the leg stump.
Slower bouncer, on middle and leg, Sufiyan Muqeem pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller than a length, on middle, Sufiyan Muqeem makes room and drags it across to mid-wicket for one.
Goes short and on off, Sufiyan Muqeem looks to ramp but misses.

OUT! TAKEN! That should be the game for New Zealand! The break in play brings New Zealand the last big fish in Tayyab Tahir. Jacob Duffy bangs the surface short of a length and outside off, Tayyab Tahir gets on top of his toes and slices it straight to deep point. Tim Seifert takes a few steps to his left and gobbles up a simple catch around his chest height.
Tayyab Tahir c T Seifert b J Duffy 33 (31b 2x4 1x6)
Full, on off, Tayyab Tahir drills his drive but stright to cover.
FOUR! Top shot. Tayyab Tahir is keeping the game alive for Pakistan! Short of a good length and well outside off, Tayyab Tahir has to reach for it, and he does. Cuts it over point for a boundary.
Keeps it well outside off, on a good length, Tayyab Tahir tries to reach for it but misses on making any connection.
Outside off, on a length, Tahir cuts it to point for a single.
On the pads, on a length, Akif Javed tries to work it fine but misses. The ball clips his pads and rolls behind to the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
No Hat trick but what a lovely ball! On a hard length, on middle and nipping back in sharply to beat the inside edge and wrap Akif high on the waist.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bang, Bang! One brings two in a flash, and Ben Sears is on a Hat Trick! Hits the surface hard, on a back of a length, on middle and off and gets the ball to shoot up at good pace. Mohammad Wasim is taken aback and sticks his bat in front to make a block. The ball takes the splice and lobs straight to Will O'Rourke at short third, who takes a simple catch.
Mohammad Wasim c W O'Rourke b B Sears 0 (1b 0x4 0x6)

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A fine use of a review from New Zealand! On a length, down leg, Naseem Shah looks to flick it but misses. The ball goes off his gloves to the left of the keeper, and Mitchell Hay moves to that side and takes a good catch low to his left. The keeper is up in celebration for a caught behind, but the umpire hasn't moved. New Zealand have decided to review it. The UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the glove, and the third umpire also checks if the keeper has collected it cleanly, and he has.
Naseem Shah c M Hay b B Sears 17 (13b 1x4 1x6)
WIDE! Short of a length again, angling into the batter, down leg, Naseem Shah hops inside the line and looks to help it on its way but misses.
Short of a length, over middle, Tahir angles it to short third for a single.
Full and outside off, Tayyab Tahir cuts it to deep point for a single. A very good over for Pakistan. 14 runs come off it.
Almost a yoker, outside off, Naseem Shah digs it out with an angled bat face and almost manages to squeeze it past backward point. One run taken.
FOUR! Thumped! On a length, around off with good pace, Naseem Shah swats it over mid off to his left for a boundary.
On a length, on off, Tahir steers it to backward point for a single.
SIX! BANG! Short and on middle, Tayyab Tahir pulls it over deep square leg for a biggie.

A bix mixup but luckily no harm done. Short of a length, outside off, Naseem Shah has a swing and gets an inside edge that goes to the left of the keeper, Mitchell Hay. Tayyab Tahir sets himself off for the run and almost reaches Naseem at the batting end. The throw isn't too great, and the bowler wasn't backing up, which allows Naseem Shah to get through to the other end.
Back of a length, on off, Naseem Shah dabs it to backward point for a single.9 runs come off this over. Pakistan need 69 more runs off 36 balls.
Short one, around off, with pace taken off, Naseem Shah throws everything at it but gets an under edge that drops down on the pitch, going nowhere.
Slower one, full and on middle, Tayyab Tahir works it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Goes into the surface and on a back of a length, over middle, Naseem Shah steers it to backward point for one.
Short and on middle, Tayyab Tahir pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
WIDE! Daryl Mitchell takes pace off and drops it short but down leg.
FOUR! Superb shot! Daryl Mitchell goes short and over off, Tayyab Tahir makes some room and ramps it through the gap between short third and backward point.
Short and outside off, Naseem Shah swats it over the bowler's head for a brace.
Hits the length hard, on off, gets some extra bounce, shaping away, Naseem Shah has a poke but misses.

SIX! He got hold of that one! Touch fuller, on middle, anglnig in a bit. Naseem Shah clears his front leg away and smacks it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie. He knew the moment he hit that and did not bother looking at it.
A bouncer now, on middle, Naseem Shah tries to ramp it away but misses.
Short of a length and on middle, Naseem Shah guides it to point.
Slower one, on a length and on off, Tayyab Tahir looks to play but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls to the off side. A quick single is taken.
Flatter, full and on middle, Tayyab Tahir knocks it towards mid on for one.
Another short delivery, on leg, Naseem Shah flicks it to deep square leg for a run.

OUT! TAKEN! Michael Bracewell gets a wicket now! He slows it up, short and on off, and turns away. Faheem Ashraf backs away to cut it but only manages to get a top edge. Tim Seifert at backward point runs to his right and dives to take a brilliant catch. Pakistan are 176/6, still needing 89 runs in 50 balls!
Faheem Ashraf c T Seifert b M Bracewell 3 (4b 0x4 0x6)
Tossed up, full and on middle, Faheem Ashraf steers it to point.
Flighted, full and on off, grips and turns away, Faheem Ashraf plays all over it.
Short again, on leg, Tayyab Tahir nudges it to short fine for a single.
Short but down the leg side, Tayyab Tahir leaves it alone. Wided.
Hard length and on off, Tayyab Tahir runs it down to third man for one.

Buzzers! Fuller and on off, Faheem Ashraf knocks it towards mid off for a single. Michael Bracewell picks up the and hits the stumps at the bowler's end, but Ashraf is in. The ball deflects away in the deep and allows a couple of extra runs.
A bouncer, but too high for the batter, Faheem Ashraf leaves it alone. Wided.

OUT! TAKEN! That's the wicket New Zealand wanted! A massive blow for Pakistan, and that is probably the last nail in the coffin for them. Jacob Duffy bowls a slower one, full and just around off. Mohammad Rizwan goes down and throws everything at it to slog it away. However, he loses balance completely and only manages to get a top edge. Mitchell Hay, the keeper, calls for it, moves forward to settle under it and pouches it safely. Pakistan lose half their side now!
Mohammad Rizwan (c) c M Hay b J Duffy 37 (32b 2x4 1x6)
On a length and on middle, Tayyab Tahir pats it in front of point for a single.
Oh..that's fiery! Jacob Duffy bangs in a quick and sharp bouncer, on middle, takes off and nips back in, Tayyab Tahir just about sways away from it.
Back of a length and on for, Mohammad Rizwan drags it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Drags his length back, on middle, turns a long way into the leg side, Tayyab Tahir nudges it to short fine. Pakistan needs 97 runs in the last ten overs!
Quicker, full and on middle, turns in, Mohammad Rizwan tries to paddle it away but gets a glove on it. It deflects off the keeper's gloves towards square leg. They cross.
Flatter, full and on middle, Tayyab Tahir works it to square leg for one.
Short again, on off, Mohammad Rizwan backs away and punches it through covers for another run.
Floated, short and on off, Tayyab Tahir uses his feet and steers it to point for a run.
Short and on leg, Mohammad Rizwan clips it towards square leg for a single.
Bangs this hard into the pitch, outside off, Tayyab Tahir tries to upper cut it but misses. That was there to be put away.
Hard length and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan guides it through point for a run.
SIX! That is outta here! Pitched up and on middle, angling in. Mohammad Rizwan picks it up nicely and uses his strong wrists to whip it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Fuller and around off, Mohammad Rizwan drives it firmly towards sweeper covers for a brace.
A slower one, short of a length and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan looks to cut but misses.
Back of a length and on off, Tayyab Tahir punches it through covers for a single.
Continues to bowl short, on middle this time, Tayyab Tahir punches it to long on for one more.
Another short delivery, angling into leg, Mohammad Rizwan pats it to mid-wikcet for one.
Quicker, short once more, on middle, Tayyab Tahir works it through square leg for a run.
Drags his length back, on off, Tayyab Tahir dabs it to short third.
Short again, on middle, Mohammad Rizwan stays back and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Floated, short and on middle, Tayyab Tahir nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Much-needed one for Pakistan! Ben Sears bangs this into the pitch, on middle, does not bounce much. Mohammad Rizwan gets on top of it and heaves it to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Five dots in a row! Short of a length and on off, Mohammad Rizwan dabs it to point.
Fuller and on off, Mohammad Rizwan drives it straight where Ben Sears gets a hand to it on his follow-through.
Back of a length and on middle, angling in, Mohammad Rizwan goes down to hook it away but misses.
Pitched up and on middle, Mohammad Rizwan drills it down the ground where it hits the stumps a the other end and goes nowhere.
Full and on middle, Mohammad Rizwan tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Rizwan nudges it to mid on and runs off a quick single.
WIDE! An off-cutter, on a length but down the leg side, Rizwan misses his flick shot. Called a wide.
Excellent running between the wickets! Hard length, with pace taken off, around middle, Mohammad Rizwan tucks it with soft hands towards mid-wicket and steals two runs.
Full and on the pads, Tahir flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Slightly fuller and around middle, Rizwan nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, around off, Tayyab Tahir pats it down towards backward point for a single.
On a good length, around middle, Mohammad Rizwan swipes it to deep square leg for a single.
Dragged length, around off, Tayyab Tahir defends it to cover.
Nagging length, around middle, Tayyab Tahir drops it down to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan lose their fourth, and they are in trouble here! Ben bowls it on a hard length and around middle and leg. Salman Agha moves across and looks to pick it up. He flicks it but gets a top edge instead that goes to deep fine leg. Jacob Duffy goes back a bit and takes it just inside the ropes. Pakistan are 135/4.
Salman Agha c J Duffy b B Sears 11 (11b 2x4 0x6)
Full and on middle, Rizwan flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Nearly a chopped on! On a hard length, around off, Salman Agha looks to cut it but gets an underedge that goes past the off stump towards square leg for a single.

FIVE WIDES! On a good length, but down the leg side, Salman Agha shuffles across and looks to tickle it but misses. The keeper dives in to his left but gets his fingertips on it as the ball runs away to the boundary.
Good length, around off, Rizwan taps it towards cover and steals a single. Good running between the wickets by both batters!
Short and wide outside off, Mohammad Rizwan cuts it to deep point for a single.
Short of a length, around off, Salman Agha looks to pull it but gets an outside edge that hits his shoulder and goes towards backward point for a single.
WIDE! A bouncer, angling into the body of the batter, Salman Agha ducks under it. Called a wide.
Back of a length, around off, Rizwan cuts it to deep point for a single.
FOUR! STREAKY! On a good length, around middle, with pace taken off, Mohammad Rizwan goes on his knee and looks to sweep it. Gets a top edge that flies over the keeper for a boundary.
Full and on the pads, Rizwan flicks it to mid on. He wants to have a single but is sent back by his partner.
Hard length, around middle, Mohammad Rizwan swipes it in the gap towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
A bumper, around midde, Salman Agha ducks under it.
Short of a length, around off, Salman Agha leaves it alone.
FOUR! ANOTHER TOP SHOT! Full again and outside off, Salman Agha comes forward and presents the full face of the bat. He drives it to the left of mid off for a boundary.
A bouncer, around middle, Salman Agha ducks under it.
BEATEN! Dragged length and outside off, Salman Agha looks to cut it but misses.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Abbas lands it full and touch outside off, Salman Agha leans on and drives it to the left of the bowler for a boundary. TOO STRAIGHT DOWN THE GROUND!
Full again and around off, Salman Agha drives it and beats the diving cover fielder to his right for a single.
Full and around middle, Salman tucks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Daryl Mitchell has given New Zealand the biggest wicket as Babar Azam is gone after making a fifty! He bowls it on a back of a length and around off, on the left shoulder of the batter. Babar Azam goes back and pulls it. He makes a good connection, but it goes straight to deep mid-wicket where Tim Seifert takes a simple catch. Salman Agha is the next batter in for Pakistan.
Babar Azam c T Seifert b D Mitchell 50 (58b 4x4 1x6)
Back of a length, around middle, Babar drops it down into the pitch for no run.
Full and outside off, Rizwan drives it to deep cover for a single.

Touch fuller and around middle, Babar Azam comes forward and nudges it wide of mid-wicket for a single. He completes his fifty and this is a fine knock from a class player but he knows that his job isn't done yet as it is a big chase and he will have to stay till the end.
Short of a length, around middle, Mohammad Rizwan hops up and drops it down to mid-wicket. He wants to have a quick single but is sent back by his partner.
On a length, around off, Babar taps it down towards cover and picks up a quick single.
FOUR! PURE TIMING! Back of a length, around middle, Babar Azam goes back and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a boundary. He moves to 48 now.
Hard length, around off, Babar Azam pats it down to backward point.
Short of a length, angling into the body of the batter, Mohammad Rizwan goes back and pulls it to deep fine leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off, Babar Azam cuts it to deep point for a single. 100 comes up for Pakistan.
On a length, around leg, Babar makes room and runs it down to third man for a single.

On a good length, around middle, Babar Azam drives it to extra cover and wants to have a quick single but the fielder is quick there, who hits the direct hit at the non-striker's end but Rizwan was in.
Hard length, around off, Rizwan runs it down to deep third for a single to get off the mark.

OUT! CAUGHT! An excellent catch from the skipper of New Zealand that has ended the inning of Usman Khan for 12(17) and Pakistan are 97/2. Abbas provides a breakthrough as he bowls it on short of a length from over the wicket, around middle, Usman Khan clears out his front leg and looks to pull it to the leg side. The ball gets big on him, and he only manages to get a top edge towards square leg. Michael Bracewell runs in to his right from mid-wicket a couple of yards and puts in a full stretched dive to catch it just inches above the ground. A Superb Catch!
Usman Khan c M Bracewell b M Abbas 12 (17b 1x4 0x6)
Back of a length, around leg, Babar Azam pulls it down to deep backward square leg for one.
Touch full and around off, Usman Khan drives it to wide mid off for a quick single.
Angles it into the right-hander, on a back of a length, Usman Khan clips it to fine leg for a single.
A bouncer, over off, Usman Khan sways away and lets it pass.
Back of a length, on off, Babar Azam punches it to cover for one.

FOUR! A boundary from Babar Azam after a long time. That should break some shackles. Short of a length, it doesn't rise as much as Will O'Rourke would have hoped for. Babar Azam stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full and on middle, Babar Azam drops it down in front of mid-wicket.
Short and on middle and leg, Usman Khan swivels back and pulls it to fine leg for one.
Nice and straight, on a length, Babar Azam shows the full face of the bat and blocks. Good start from Abbas. Just the 4 runs off his first over.
Fuller in length, on middle and leg, Usman Khan clips it to fine leg for a single.
Short one, over middle, Usman Khan crouches low and looks to pull but misses. Absolutely no control on that shot.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Babar Azam tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Goes full and on off, Babar Azam with very soft hands taps it down the deck.
Errs in line first up and serves it on the pads, on a length, Babar Azam tickles it to fine leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Much-needed boundary for Pakistan! Will O'Rourke goes full for once again, and on off, Usman Khan clears his front leg out and crunches it through covers for a boundary.
Short and on off, Usman Khan whips it aerially over point. The ball plugs in the outfield near the ropes and the batters take two runs.
Very similar line and length to the previous one, but Babar angles the bat face and steers it to deep third for one.
Bangs it on a back of a length, outside off, Babar Azam has a fiddle at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length, on off, Babar Azam stabs it down the deck.
Full, on middle, Babar Azam drives it to mid on.
A bit short and on off, Usman Khan punches it to the left of mid-wicket.
Full, on middle, Usman Khan taps it to mid-wicket.
WIDE! Slips it full and down leg. Usman Khan tries to scoop it behind but doesn't connect.
Short and turning into middle and leg, Usman Khan tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full, on middle and leg, Babar Azam works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Gives the ball some air and keeps it full, on off, Babar Azam lunges to block.
Going on with the arm, on the pads, Usman Khan tucks it to the leg side and rotates the strike over.
Gets off the mark! Short and outside off, Usman Khan dabs it to deep backward point for one. End of a tight over from Ben Sears!
Lovely bowling! Short one over middle, Usman Khan looks to pull but is way too early and misses out.
Back of a length, on off, Usman Khan chops it to cover off the inner half of the bat.
That's a hostile welcome into the crease for the concussion substitute! A sharp bouncer directed at the left shoulder, Usman Khan sways away from the line.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Sears finally provides New Zealand with the breakthrough they were after for so long. He bangs it into the surface and angles it into the batter, on middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique is hurried a bit because of the sheer pace, but he still tries to pull. Hits it straight down the throat of Jacob Duffy at fine leg, who takes a nice reverse cup catch.
Abdullah Shafique c J Duffy b B Sears 33 (56b 3x4 0x6)
Short one, on middle, Babar Azam times his pull beautifully but straight to deep square leg for a single.
A tad bit short and on the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Drifting into middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique tucks it to mid-wicket.
Dealing in singles and quite easily at the moment! Tossed up, on off, Babar Azam works it to long on and rotates the strike over.
Full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique steps down the track and eases it to long on for a run.
Tossed up, on off, Babar Azam drives it to long on for a single.
Slanting on leg, Abdullah Shafique helps it on its way with a sweep to fine leg for one.
Lands it on a back of a length, on off, Abdullah Shafique knocks it to the right of backward point and takes a run.
Length, on off, Abdullah Shafique taps it to backward point.
Width offered outside off, fuller in length, Babar Azam reaches for it and cuts it to deep backward point for one.
Angles it into the pads, on a length, Abdullah Shafique clips it to square leg and picks up a single.
Full again, just around off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to cover.
Full and on off, Babar Azam taps it to the off side and takes a single.
Slows it up, full and on off, turns in. Babar Azam uses his feet to play at it but gets hit on the pads as the ball rolls towards cover-point. They cross.
Flighted, full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique swipes it through square leg for one.
Short and on middle, Babar Azam punches it to long on for a single.
Flatter, full and on middle, turns in a bit, Babar Azam goes down to sweep but misses. It was not far away from the stumps.
Floated, full and on middle, Babar Azam uses his feet and clips it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on leg, Babar Azam tucks it to short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam steers it to third man for one.
Close! Hits the length hard, on middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to play but gets a bottom edge just past the stumps towards short fine. They cross.
Bangs this into the pitch, on off, Babar Azam punches it through covers for a run.
Hard length and around off, Abdullah Shafique guides it to third man for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique dabs it to point.
Short of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique stabs it towards covers.
Short and on leg, Abdullah Shafique nudges it to deep mid-wicket for one. That also brings up the 50-run partnership between these two batters.
A bit quicker, full and on off, Babar Azam taps it towards covers for one.

A big shout for LBW, but turned down! Flighted, full and on middle, turns in. Babar Azam sets out to fend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Michael Bracewell thinks about the review but does not take it.
FOUR! Streaky! Flatter, short and on middle, Babar Azam stays back to cut but gets an outside edge to the third man fence for a boundary.
SIX! Excellent use of the feet! Floated, full and around middle. Babar Azam dances down the track to get to the pitch of it and tonls it over the bowler's head for a biggie.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique eases it towards long on for a single.
Good length and on off, Babar Azam works it off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
Fuller and around off, Babar Azam drives it firmly through covers for a brace.
Uppish but safe! Short of a length and on middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to pull but mistimes it just over mid-wikcet for a run.
Full and on the pads, Babar Azam clips it through square leg for a single.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam blocks it to the off side.
Pitched up and angling into the leg side, Babar Azam misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads to the keeper. However, the umpire calls it a wide.
Fuller one and around off, Babar Azam looks to drive but gets it from the bottom edge back towards the bowler.
Slows it up, full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique turns it to the leg side.
Quicker, full and on off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Looped up, full and on middle, Babar Azam uses his feet and drills it to long on for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Babar Azam pushes it down the pitch.
Flatter, short and on middle, Babar Azam moves back and pats it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Babar Azam tucks it to short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique pats it to short covers.
Fuller one and on off, Abdullah Shafique knocks it towards mid on.
Hits the length hard and on off, Abdullah Shafique looks to punch it away but gets a bottom edge onto his pads.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, on off, nips back in sharply, Abdullah Shafique looks to play at it but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Back of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it out as the ball bounces off the pitch and hits his bat again but goes nowhere.
Short of a length but way outside off, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone. Wided.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam drives it to mid off for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique stays back and blocks it out.
Swing and a miss! Jacob Duffy bangs this one into the pitch, on middle, gets some extra bounce. Abdullah Shafique backs away and slashes at it but misses.
Short of a length and on off, Abdullah Shafique dabs it to point.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Jacob Duffy goes a bit too full, on middle, angling in, Abdullah Shafique presents the full face of the bat and plays the on-drive to perfection towards the long on fence for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique strides out and blocks it out towards point.
Hard length and on middle, Abdullah Shafique pats it to mid-wicket.
Goes fuller and on the pads, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW but is not given by the umpire.

WIDE! Sprays it down the leg side on a full length, Abdullah Shafique swings at it but misses. The keeper Mitchell Hay does well to make a dive to his left to collect the ball to save a couple of runs for his side. Still, a wide is called.
Dragged length, around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to cover.
BEAUTY! Hard length and around off, nips away for a bit, Abdullah Shafique gets squared up in his defence and gets beaten on the outside edge.
WIDE! Hits the deck hard with a short-of-a-length ball, but down the leg side, Abdullah Shafique looks to pull it but misses. Called a wide.
Nagging length, around off, Abdullah Shafique drops it down to cover.
FOUR! CHIPPED! Touch full and on the pads, angling in, Abdullah Shafique picks it up and flicks it aerially over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off, Abdullah Shafique pats it down to cover.
On a good length but on the pads, Babar Azam flicks it past the mid on fielder, who gives it a chase and cuts it off for a couple of runs.
Hard length and around off, Babar drops it down to cover.
FOUR! PUNISHED! Back of a length and around leg, Babar Azam stands tall and whips it to deep backward square leg for a boundary.
Full and around off, Babar Azam drives it back to the bowler who stops it on his follow-through.
Nagging length, around off, jags back in sharply, Babar Azam gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it on the back pad after getting deflected off the gloves.
Full and around middle, Babar Azam flicks it to mid on.
Dragged length, just outside off, Abdullah Shafique pats it down to backward point.
On a length and wide outside off, just over the tramline, Abdullah Shafique doesn't offer any shot at it. He looks at the umpire for a wide call but the umpire is convinced that it is a legal ball.
Nagging length and outside off, with pace taken off, Abdullah Shafique chops it out to cover off the back foot.
Back of a length, around off, with an extra bounce, Abdullah Shafique gets squared up as he looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge towards cover point.
Hard length and outside off, Babar Azam throws his hands at it and looks to cut but gets it through the outer half of the bat to deep third man aerially for a single.
WIDE! Sprays it down the leg side, slightly fuller and comes back in, Babar Azam leaves it. Called a wide.
On a good length and outside off, Babar Azam leaves it alone.

FOUR! GOOD SHOT! Touch full from Duffy, around off, Abdullah Shafique comes forward and drives it to the left of the bowler aerially. Duffy tries to take a catch by extending his left arm but he fails to do so and the ball goes to the boundary.
Hard length, around off, nips back in sharply, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick it but gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it on the box.
A bumper, angling into the body of the batter, Abdullah Shafique ducks under it.
Nagging length and around off and middle, Abdullah nudges it to mid-wicket.
Dragged length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to drive it on the up but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Nice and full, but on the pads, touch straight from Duffy, Abdullah Shafique leans on and flicks it in the gap towards mid-wicket. The fielder gives it a chase and cuts it off to restrict the batters for a couple of runs.
Short and wide of outside off, Babar looks to cut it but gets it through the bottom part of the bat to cover.

Good Effort! Short of a length and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique hops up and cuts it off late towards deep third man. Ben Sears runs in to his right and puts in a dive to save one run. Three runs taken
WIDE! Slightly fuller but down the leg side, Abdullah Shafique misses his flick shot and the keeper collects it to his left with a good dive.
Good carry to the keeper! Back of a length and well outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to play it at first but withdraws his shot in the end.

A tight single! Dragged length and around off, Imam-ul-Haq taps it down towards cover and runs off for a quick single. The fielder picks it up and makes a throw to the non-striker's end, but it has hit Imam on his jaw under the grill of the helmet, and he looks in pain.
BEATEN! A bit fuller and just outside off, nips back in after pitching, Imam-ul-Haq goes for an expansive drive but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Touch full but wide outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Nagging length, around off, Abdullah Shafique drops it down to cover.

JAFFA! On a good length and around off, angling in at first but it seams away after pitching a bit. Abdullah Shafique comes forward to defend it but gets squared up. He gets beaten on the outside edge in the end.
Hard length and around leg, Abdullah Shafique nudges it wide of deep fine leg and picks up a couple of runs.
Much fuller and around off, Abdullah Shafique flicks it to mid on.
Slightly fuller but on the pads, Abdullah Shafique tucks it to mid-wicket.
Begins with a good-length ball, outside off, shaping away, Abdullah Shafique shoulders his arms on it.
Short of a length, around off. Imam-ul-Haq drops it down towards cover and wants to have a quick single but is sent back by his partner through halfway.
Back of a length and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it.
On a good length, on the fourth stump, Imam-ul-Haq shoulders his arms on it.
Nagging length, in the channel outside off, Imam-ul-Haq watches it carefully and decides to not offer any shot at it.
WIDE! Sprays it down the leg side, on a hard length, Imam-ul-Haq misses his tickle shot. Called a wide.

Pakistan and Abdullah Shafique are underway! Short of a length and well outside off, Abdullah Shafique hops up and opens bat face to cut it off late. The ball goes towards deep third on the bounce for a single.
Starts with a back-of-a-length ball, outside off, seaming away, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.

OUT! Akif Javed finishes with a four-fer! He takes pace off again, short of length and outside off. Michael Bracewell tries to cut but gets a top edge behind short third. Naseem Shah runs backwards, keeps his eyes under the swirling ball and takes a fantastic catch diving forward. New Zealand ends up with 264/8!
Michael Bracewell (c) c N Shah b A Javed 59 (40b 1x4 6x6)
A slower bouncer, outside off, Michael Bracewell swings at it but fails to connect.
SIX! BOOM! Salt to the wounds! Akif Javed bangs this short and on middle, sits up nicely for the batter. Michael Bracewell stands tall and smacks it over the wide long on fence for half a dozen runs.

DROPPED! This could be costly for Pakistan! Fuller one and on middle, Michael Bracewell looks to slog it away to the leg side but gets a top edge. Tayyab Tahir at extra covers tries to settle under it and reverse cup but spills it out.

SIX! FIFTY FOR BRACEWELL! He gets to it with a bang as well! A captain's knock and he has been superb in this series. Back of a length and on middle. Michael Bracewell picks up the length early and whacks it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.

Put down! A tough chance, though! Short of a length and on off, Ben Sears slaps it down the pitch. Akif Javed fails to react quickly as the ball hits his left hand and deflects towards covers. A single is taken.
Short again and on middle, Ben Sears pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
A low full toss, outside off, Michael Bracewell drills it to sweeper covers for a single. 250 up for New Zealand!
Back of a length and on off, Michael Bracewell looks to pull but gets a top edge over the bowler's head. The batters get two again as the fielder from long off is a bit late to get to the ball.

Sloppy! Short of a length and outside off, Ben Sears punches it towards covers. Akif Javed tries to slide and stop it with his foot but lets it through and allows three runs. Also, Michael Bracewell is back on strike.

OUT! TAKEN! Faheem Ashraf strikes! He bangs this one hard into the pitch, slower as well. Mitchell Hay backs away and tries to swat it away but fails to get on top of the bounce. It flies off the top edge straight down to the throat of Babar Azam at long on, who makes no mistake. New Zealand are 244/7!
Mitchell Hay (wk) c B Azam b F Ashraf 8 (8b 0x4 0x6)

Pakistan have been penalised for not completing the overs in time, and now they will have to call an extra fielder back in the circle for the last two overs. Good effort in the deep! Short of a length and on middle, Mitchell Hay pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket. Salman Agha runs to his right and dives to push it back inside just in time. Two runs taken.
Short of a length and outside off, takes off, Michael Bracewell tries to cut but gets a top edge over short third for a brace.

NO BALL AND FOUR! What happened there? Akif Javed loses his grip and bowls a full toss over the head of the batter and down the leg side. Michael Bracewell lets it go and Mohammad Rizwan also fails to stop it from going to the fine leg fence for a boundary. Free Hit up next...
Fuller and on off, Mitchell Hay drills it hard down the pitch where it hits Javed's left foot and rolls to long off. They cross.
Pitched up and outside off again, Michael Bracewell throws the kitchen sink at it, gets a top edge that just goes over point. Two runs taken.
Slower one, full and outside off, Michael Bracewell slices it wide of long off for a brace.
Akif Javed bowls a perfect yorker, on middle, angling in, Michael Bracewell just about manages to dig it out.
Pace off, back of a length and on middle, Mitchell Hay pats it towards mid-wicket for a single.

SIX! Into the crowd! Naseem Shah misses his yorker and bowls this right in the slot, on middle. Michael Bracewell stays deep inside his crease, gets under it and dispatches it over the long on fence for a biggie.
Fuller and on middle, Mitchell Hay drives it to mid off for one.
A bouncer but down the leg side, Mitchell Hay leaves it alone. Wided.
Naseem Shah follows the batter and hits the length hard, outside off. Michael Bracewell thinks about the scoop but has to adjust and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Slower again, back of length and on leg, Mitchell Hay looks to pull but it lobs up off his forearm towards point. A leg bye is taken.
Tries the slower bouncer, but this is down the leg side, Mitchell Hay lets it go. Wided.
Fires in a yorker, on off, Michael Bracewell digs it out towards mid off for a single.
Short of a length and on middle and off, Michael Bracewell flat-bats it wide of long on for a brace.
Hard length and on off, Mitchell Hay steers it through point for a brace.
Bangs this into the pitch, outside off, Michael Bracewell slaps it on the bounce to long off for one.
Slower one, full and on off, Michael Bracewell swings hard at it but gets an inisd edge on his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Short of a length and on middle, Mitchell Hay swats it to square leg for a single.
Loses his line completely and bowls it well outside off, almost out of the pitch, Mitchell Hay leaves it alone. Wided.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Akif Javed gets his third now! He serves this full and well outside off. Muhammad Abbas tries to reach out for it and slashes hard but only manages a thin bottom edge behind where Mohammad Rizwan makes no mistake. New Zealand six down now!
Muhammad Abbas c M Rizwan b A Javed 11 (11b 0x4 1x6)
Back of a length and outside off, Muhammad Abbas looks to heave it away but gets a bottom edge back towards the keeper.
A low full toss, on middle, Muhammad Abbas swipes it off the inside half of the bat to shot fine for one. Just 4 runs off the over!
Bangs it into the pitch, on middle, Muhammad Abbas backs away and swats it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Clever bowling! Naseem Shah takes pace off again, short of a length and on leg, Muhammad Abbas fails to read it and misses his pull.
Right in the blockhole, on middle, Michael Bracewell jams it out towards long off for a single.
Nice change of pace, back of a length and outside off, Michael Bracewell looks to pull it away but goes through it early and misses.
Naseem Shah nails the yorker, just on off, Michael Bracewell fails to dig it out. Shah appeals for a caught behind, but no one is interested other than him.
Good reply! Mohammad Wasim hits the length hard, on off, nips back in sharply, Muhammad Abbas looks to guide it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
SIX! BANG! That's sheer power! Fuller one and on middle, in the slot as well. Muhammad Abbas clears his front leg away and smokes it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Back of a length and on off, Muhammad Abbas looks to pull it away but mistimes it towards mid-wicket. He missed out there.
Slower one, on a length and on off, Michael Bracewell tucks it to the leg side for a run.
Fuller one and angling into leg, Michael Bracewell looks to whip it away but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Hard length and on leg, Muhammad Abbas flicks it through square leg for a single. 200 UP FOR THE KIWIS!
SIX! Brute force! 18 runs come off this over despite a wicket! Short again, on off, Michael Bracewell stands tall and thumps it over long on for consecutive sixes.
SIX! Michael Bracewell showing his class! Akif Javed bashes the deck, angles the short one, on middle and leg, Michael Bracewell pulls it over fine leg for a six.
Back of a length, over off, Muhammad Abbas miscues the cut but manages to squeeze a single as the ball goes in front of cover.
Almost another one! Similar line but gets a bit more bounce and shape that leaves the batter from outside off. Muhammad Abbas has a poke at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The bowling change works wonders for Pakistan, and New Zealand lose half their side now for 186 runs. Akif Javed bangs the deck, on a back of a length and keeps the line of attack, outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets on top of his toes and looks to punch it through the off side but only manages to get a thick outside edge that goes straight to the keeper, Mohammad Rizwan.
Daryl Mitchell c M Rizwan b A Javed 43 (53b 3x4 1x6)
WIDE! Way too short and over off.
FOUR! A hostile welcome back into the attack for Akif Javed! Back of a length, outside off, Daryl Mitchell opens the bat face and runs it past short third to his right for a boundary.
Short of a length, on off, Bracewell punches it to cover.
SIX! Picked up and dispatched! Angling in, around leg, on a back of a length, Michael Bracewell whips it behind and clears deep fine leg fence for a biggie.
Keeps it at the stumps, on a length, blocked down the deck by Bracewell.
WIDE! Angling in but down leg, on a length. Mohammad Wasim will have to reload that one.
Very full, on the feet of the batter, Daryl Mitchell flicks it straight to short fine leg and Michael Bracewell calls him through for a quick run.
Good length, on middle, Michael Bracewell tucks it square on the leg side for a single.
Full, on middle and leg, Michael Bracewell clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! Floated full, on off, Michael Bracewell pumps it over mid on and gets his first boundary.
Drops it a bit too short and on off, Bracewell punches it but cannot get it past mid off.
Much fuller, on off, Daryl Mitchell sweeps it behind to fine leg for one.
Full, on off, Michael Bracewell eases the drive to cover and picks up a single.
Full, on middle, Michael Bracewell drives it to point.

Full and on off, Michael Bracewell drives it to the right of the cover fielder who dives to make a stop. Keeps it down to just a single. End of a fine over from Naseem Shah! Just the one run and a wicket off it.
Much fuller, on the pads, Michael Bracewell tries to flick but misses onto his pads.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Michael Bracewell tucks it to mid-wicket.
Attacking the stumps, on a fuller length, Bracewell pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, on middle, Michael Bracewell turns it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan get a timely wicket, and New Zealand lose their 4th one. Naseem Shah bowls it on a length, on middle and off, Tim Seifert swings across in an attempt to heave but does so a bit too early. Hits it off the lower half of the bat and gets more elevation than the distance. Tayyab Tahir at deep mid-wicket keeps his eyes on the ball and, with precise judgement, stays inches within the rope to take a fine reverse cup catch.
Tim Seifert c T Tahir b N Shah 26 (29b 1x4 1x6)
Slower through the air, full and outside off, Daryl Mitchell swings but misses out.
Drags the length down, on off, Daryl Mitchell punches it to cover.
Full, on middle, Daryl Mitchell shuffles across and ramps it over the keeper's head for a couple more runs.
FOUR! Daryl Mitchell is switching gears! Full and on middle, he slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
In the air, but falls safe. A bit more flight, on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to sweep it. Gets a top edge that falls around the vacant deep square leg region for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, on middle and leg, turning in, Daryl Mitchell tries to tickle it fine but misses. The ball brushes his thigh and goes past the keeper to his left for a brace.
Full, at the toes, Daryl Mitchell works it to long on for a single.
Another yorker, this time at these stumps, Tim Seifert jams it to cover and takes a single. 50-run partnership is up between these two.
Slower yorker, just outside off, Tim Seifert tries to dig it out but misses to make a connection.
Too full, on off, Daryl Mitchell drives it to cover for a single.
Follows up with a hard-length delivery, on middle and off, Daryl Mitchell drops it down the deck.
SIX! Smoked! Naseem Shah comes back into the attack and goes short, on middle. Sits up nicely for Daryl Mitchell, who swivels back and pulls it over square leg for a biggie.
Tossed up, around off, Tim Seifert taps it to short third.
Full, on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell tucks it in front of deep mid-wicket for a quick single.
Drops it short and turns it into the batter, on middle and leg, Tim Seifert rocks back and knocks it through covers for a run.
Goes full, on middle, Tim pushes it to mid off.
Loopy full toss, at the stumps, Daryl Mitchell scoops it to fine leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Tim Seifert punches it to deep cover for one.
A low full toss, outside off, Daryl Mitchell drills it back to the bowler who stops it on his follow-through.
Back of a length, around off, Mitchell pushes it to cover.

On a good length and outside off, Tim Seifert clears out his front leg and lofts it over cover for a single. The skipper, Mohammad Rizwan, isn't happy with the effort of the fielder in the deep as he didn't go for the catch.
A good follow-up yorker, around middle, Daryl Mitchell manages to dig it out to deep fine leg for a single.
On a good length, around middle, nips back in sharply, Daryl Mitchell hops up and looks to drop it down to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the front pad.
Back of a length, around off, Daryl Mitchell pulls it off the back foot but straight to mid-wicket.
A low full toss, around off, Tim Seifert jams it out to backward point.
Full and into the pads, Daryl Mitchell goes on his knee and sweeps it to deep fine leg for one.
BEATEN! A bit quicker and on a nagging length, outside off, Daryl Mitchell looks to cut it but misses.
Floated it up, around off, Tim drives it to the left of mid off for a single.
Drops it short and around off, Tim Seifert goes back and cuts it hard but straight to cover point.
Tossed it up, outside off, Daryl Mitchell goes on his knee and looks to paddle it but gets an underedge to third man for a single.
Full and outside off, Darly punches it to deep cover for a single.
Nagging length, into the pads, Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket.
A quick single! Lands it full and outside off, Tim Seifert drives it to the left of mid off and gets to the other end quickly.
Full and around middle, Mitchell drives it to the right of the bowler for a single.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Tim Seifert comes forward and drives it through covers for a single.
Back of a length and around off, Mitchell punches it to deep cover for a single.
Dragged length and around off, Tim Seifert makes room and cuts it towards sweeper cover. He picks up a couple of runs as the fielder in the deep is a bit slow to throw it to the keeper.
A loopy full ball, around off, Tim Seifert drills it back to the bowler.
Nagging length, around off, Daryl Mitchell comes forward and pushes it to long off for a single.
Floated it up, around off, Daryl drives it but straight to cover again.
Tossed it up, around off Mitchell drives it to cover.
Short and around off, Tim Seifert uses his feet and slashes it off the outer half of the bat aerially to deep backward point for a single.
Full and around off, Tim pushes it to long on for a single to end the over.

BEATEN! A good comeback by Wasim! He bowls it slightly fuller and in the channel outside off, gets to nip away a bit. Tim Seifert gets squared up as he looks to defend it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hard length and well outside off, Tim Seifert lofts it inside out over cover but doesn't time it well. However, it goes over the cover fielder and he gets a couple of runs.
SIX! POWERED AWAY! Touch short and angling into the body of the batter, Tim Seifert goes back and pulls it hard over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
BEATEN! On a back of a length and outside off, gets a bit of an extra bounce as well, Tim Seifert looks to slash at it but misses.
On a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell moves across a bit and punches it to deep cover for a single.
BEATEN! Dragged length and touch outside off, Tim Seifert goes back to cut it but misses.
Flighted it up, around leg, Daryl Mitchell goes on his knee and paddles it to deep fine leg for a single.
Full and around middle, Mitchell nudges it to wide mid-wicket.
Floated it up, around middle, Tim Seifert looks to nudge it towards mid-wicket but gets a leading edge to backward point for a single.
BEATEN! Tossed it up and outside off, turns away, Tim Seifert leans on to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Drops it short and around off, Tim Seifert goes back and punches it to extra cover.
On a good length and on the pads, Tim turns it to deep square leg and takes a single.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! Faheem lands it full and around middle, Tim Seifert comes forward and shows the full face of the bat. He drives it to the right of the bowler down the ground for a boundary. Such a lovely shot!
Hard length and around off, Tim Seifert hops up and cuts it but off the bottom part of the bat towards cover.
Back of a length and touch outside off, Mitchell pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Nagging length, and around off, Daryl Mitchell looks to punch it to the off side but gets it off the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket.
On a good length and into the stumps, Mitchell tucks it to mid-wicket.
Looped up, full and on off, Daryl Mitchell eases it to long off for one.
FOUR! Nice shot! Dragged back and well outside off. Daryl Mitchell rocks back, uses the width on offer and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Flighted, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Short and on off, Tim Seifert punches it through covers for a run.

OUT! LBW! A massive shout for LBW, but turned down! Mohammad Rizwan is literally pleading with the umpire, as it looks really close, too. Pakistan take the review. This is floated, full and on middle and leg, turns in. Rhys Mariu goes down to sweep, but this is too full for that shot, and he misses to get hit on the pads. The only thing that can save him, if it is pitching outside leg. However, UltraEdge confirms that no bat is involved, and Ball Tracking comes up three reds! Another timely wicket for Pakistan as Mariu departs for 58 off 61. The Kiwis are three down now.
Rhys Mariu lbw S Muqeem 58 (61b 6x4 2x6)
Tossed up, full and on off, Daryl Mitchell drives it to long off for a single.
Bangs it into the pitch, outside off, Rhys Mariu punches it wide of sweeper covers for a brace.
HIts the length hard, on off, Daryl Mitchell pats it towards short covers for another run. 100 up for New Zealand!
On a length and on middle, angling in, Daryl Mitchell nudges it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Daryl Mitchell stabs it in front of short covers.
Short of a length and outside off, Rhys Mariu cuts it through point for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell knocks it to mid on for a single. That brings up 2000 ODI RUNS for him!
Quicker, full and on middle, Rhys Mariu stays back and blocks it out.
FOUR! Up and over! Flighted, full and on off. Rhys Mariu moves to the leg side early to create some room, reaches out for it and lofts it beautifully over extra covers for a boundary.
Flatter, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Slows it up, full and on leg, Daryl Mitchell turns it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell goes down to paddle it away but the ball goes off his gloves onto his body and drops on the off side.
Tossed up, full and on off, Rhys Mariu drives it through covers for a single.
MAIDEN-WICKET OVER! A fine yorker now, on off, Daryl Mitchell digs it out to the off side.
Hard length and on off, Daryl Mitchell pats it in front of short covers.
Short of a length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell keeps it out on the pitch.
A bouncer, on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
On a length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Akif Javed gets the breakthrough for Pakistan! A much-needed one for the visitors as the big 78-run stand is broken now. This is a sharp and quick bouncer, on middle, takes off a bit. Henry Nicholls looks to pull it away but the ball gets big on him and takes the top edge. It flies high in the air towards deep square leg where Mohammad Wasim settles under it and takes a good catch. Nicholls walks back for 31 off 40, and New Zealand are 91/2!
Henry Nicholls c M Wasim b A Javed 31 (40b 1x4 0x6)
Short and on off, Henry Nicholls punches it through covers for one.
Slows it up, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls blocks it out.

MAIDEN ODI FIFTY FOR MARIU! An excellent knock from the youngster, and he has looked solid from the get-go here. This is a bit short and on off, Rhys Mariu steers it to short third and sets off for the run. He is not aware that the throw is at his end, but it misses the stumps, and he makes his ground.
Flighted, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls swipes it to short fine and scampers across for a run.
Floated, full and on off, Rhys Mariu gets down across and paddles it to fine leg for a single. He moves to 49 now!
Tossed up, full and on middle, Rhys Mariu taps it to short covers.
Hard length and on middle and leg, Rhys Mariu heaves it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Pitched up and on leg, Rhys Mariu blocks it out.
Short again, on middle, Henry Nicholls pulls it away nicely to deep square leg for a run.
Back of a length but down the leg side, Henry Nicholls tries to hook it away but misses. Wided.
Short of a length and on off, Henry Nicholls dabs it to point.
Full again and on middle, Henry Nicholls drills it back to the bowler.
Edged but safe! Fuller and around off, angling away, Rhys Mariu looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge down to the left of third man for a single.
Fires one, full and on middle, Rhys Mariu tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flighted, full and on off, Rhys Mariu quickly gets down on a knee and nails the reverse sweep through point for a boundary.
Drags his length back, outside off, Rhys Mariu punches it wide of sweeper covers for a brace.
Flatter, short and on middle, Rhys Mariu pats it to the left of short mid-wicket.
Floated, short and around off, turns away Henry Nicholls cuts it to deep point for a single.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls pushes it to short covers.
A low full toss, outside off, Rhys Mariu makes no contact with the ball as he looks to drive. Will feel he missed on this one for sure.
Full and on the stumps, Henry Nicholls angles it to deep third for a run.
In the air again, and just short of the fielder! Too full and on middle and leg, Rhys Mariu flicks it uppishly to the right of mid on for one.
Full, on off, Rhys Mariu firms his drive but straight to mid off.
Good length, outside off, Henry Nicholls cuts it to deep point for one.
Good running between the wickets! Hard length, on off, Rhys Mariu nudges it in front of point and charges through for a quick run.

In the air, but falls safe. A lot of half-chances created by Salman Agha already! Short and on off, Rhys Mariu backs away to cut and gets a thick outside edge that lobs to the left of short third for one.
Full, on off, Rhys Mariu lunges to block.
Tossed up, around middle and off, Henry Nicholls drives it to deep point for one.
Short and on off, Henry Nicholls slaps it hard but straight to cover.
Full, on middle, Henry Nicholls pushes it to cover.
Looped full, on middle, Henry Nicholls gets a thick outside edge in an attempt to drive it straight and beats short third to his right for two.
Length, around off, Rhys Mariu miscues his drive to the left of the bowler.
Good length, on middle and off, Henry Nicholls works it through covers for one.
Hard length, on leg, Henry Nicholls hops back to block but misses onto his pads. There is an appeal for LBW by the bowler alone and the umpire turns it down.
Short and outside off, Rhys Mariu looks to cut but chops it down the deck and in front of backward point. Henry Nicholls calls him through for a quick single.
Attacks the stumps, on a good length and gets the ball to nip back in, Rhys Mariu just about manages to block it out.
Back of a length, on off, Rhys Mariu cuts it to backward point.
Full, on middle, Henry Nicholls taps it to mid on.
Almost a wicket! Floated full, on off, Henry Nicholls drives it uppishly but manages to keep it away from the leaping cover fielder to his left. Two runs taken.
Drifting away, from around off, Henry Nicholls tries to drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Keeps it short and on off, Rhys Mariu cuts it to deep backward point for a single. The 50-run stand is up between these two batters.
Floated full, on middle, Henry Nicholls lunges to block. Gets an inside edge to square leg for one.
Comes into the attack and goes full, on middle, Henry Nicholls knocks it to mid on.
Bashes the surface yet again, on a back of a length, on leg, Henry Nicholls fails to tuck it down. The ball clips his thigh pad and goes to the leg side. The batters take a leg bye.
Bangs the deck hard, on a short of a length, over leg, Henry Nicholls ducks under it.
Good length, on middle and off, Henry Nicholls neatly works it through covers for a brace.
Goes very full, on middle, Henry Nicholls jams it out.
FOUR! Just wide enough! Fuller and outside off, Henry Nicholls reaches out and cuts it past backward point to his right for a boundary.

Top delivery! On a length, outside off, Henry Nicholls moves across and looks to play it on the leg side but the ball shapes away and he gets beaten. The ball goes off the thigh pad and Mohammad Rizwan fails to grab it to his left with a dive.
Another one that moves away, from around off, Rhys Mariu leaves it alone. That will be the end of the first Powerplay!
FOUR! As good a shot can get! Good length, on off, shaping away, Rhys Mariu creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Lovely ball! Short of a length, around off and shaping away with good bounce off the deck. Rhys Mariu looks to block but is beaten on the outside edge.
Angling into the pads, on a good length, Rhys Mariu tucks it to mid-wicket.
Hard length, at the stumps, Rhys Mariu keeps it out.
WIDE! On a length but going down leg. 50 runs up for New Zealand.
Beautiful shot! Fuller than a length and outside off, Henry Nicholls drives it past mid off. Mohammad Wasim from mid off chases the ball and slides to push it back in, saving a run for his side.
Length, on off, Rhys Mariu offers a solid front foot block.
On a length, at the stumps, Henry Nicholls tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
hard length, over middle and leg, zips through quicker and Henry Nicholls is cramped in for room. Gets hit high around the waist.
Good length, around off, Rhys Mariu works it to deep third for a single.
Short of a length, on middle, Henry Nicholls pulls it past square leg to his right. The ball loses steam around the boundary rope, and the fielder from mid-wicket chases it. Three runs taken.
Starts well, does Mohammad Wasim! Comes from around the wicket and angles it into middle and leg, on a fuller length, Henry Nicholls looks to tuck it across but gets beaten onto his pads.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Full again and around off, this time, Rhys Mariu comes forward and creams his drive in the gap towards cover for another boundary.

FOUR! TOP SHOT! Slightly fuller and on the pads, tries to follow the batter. Rhys Mariu uses his feet and flicks it towards deep backward square leg. The fielder chases it though but the ball races away to the boundary.
BEATEN! Back of a length and outside off, swings away, Rhys Mariu looks to defend it but the ball zips past the outside edge by an inch.

Good fielding! Naseem lands it full and around off, Henry Nicholls leans on and drives it in the gap towards cover. Mohammad Wasim runs in from mid off and puts in a slide to save one run. The batters take three runs.
On a good length and wide outside off, Henry Nicholls doesn't offer any shot at it.
Full and around off, Henry comes forward and drives it to mid off.
Back of a length, around off, Mariu dabs it down towards cover point for no run.
Lands it full again and around off, Rhys Mariu takes out his front leg forward and drops it down to cover. He wants to have a single but is sent back by his partner.
Bowls it slightly fuller than the previous one, around middle, Rhys Mariu defends it off the back foot.
Nagging length, around off, Rhys Mariu pats it down into the pitch, and the ball rolls away back to the bowler.
Pitches it up, around off, Rhys Mariu comes forward and defends it right under his eyes.

SIX! EFFORTLESS! Faheem bowls it on the pads, on a full length, a gentle loosener. Rhys Mariu picks it up as he leans on and flicks it with soft hands. The ball sails over the deep square leg for a biggie.
In the air... but falls safe! On a hard length and around middle, Rhys Mariu looks to chip it in to the leg side but gets a top edge that goes wide of mid-wicket. The batters take a single.
Hits the deck hard with a short-of-a-length ball, around off, Rhys Mariu looks to defend it again but gets an outside edge that goes to the gully fielder on the bounce.
BEATEN! Back of a length and just outside off, Rhys Mariu gets squared up again as he looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Slightly fuller and well outside off, Rhys Mariu gets width to open his arms as he slices it in the gap towards backward point for a boundary.
BEAUTY! On a hard length and in the channel outside off, Rhys Mariu gets squared up in trying to defend it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Nealy a chopped on! On a good length, around off, Rhys Mariu defends it with a straight but the ball rolls away under his bat and zips past the off stump.
Hard length, at hips, Henry Nicholls tucks it towards square leg and picks up a couple of runs.
Slightly fuller length and wide outside off, moving away from the batter, Henry Nicholls watches it but decides to not offer any shot at it.
Nagging length, around middle, Henry drops it down to mid on.
Touch fuller and just outside off, Henry Nicholls comes forward and drives it. He connects it well but the ball goes straight to the extra cover fielder.
WIDE! On a dragged length but down the leg side, swinging back into the left-handed batter, Henry Nicholls misses his tickle shot. Called a wide.
Leg bye! Lands it full and around middle, Rhys Mariu misses his flick shot and gets hit on the front pad. He gets a single for leg bye as the ball rolls away wide of square leg.

Begins with a yorker, around off, Rhys Mariu drils it towards mid off. Sufiyan Muqeem runs in to his left and slides to stop the ball but makes a fumble there which allows a couple of runs for the batters.

OUT! CAUGHT! A sharp catch has ended the short stay of Nick Kelly as he goes for 3(9) and New Zealand are 13/1. Naseem bowls it fuller and on the pads, gets it to swing back in, Nick Kelly lunges and flicks it. He connects it well, but towards short mid-wicket. Abdullah Shafique puts in a dive to his right there and picks it up just above the ground. The precise field placement has provided this early wicket for Pakistan.
Nick Kelly c A Shafique b N Shah 3 (9b 0x4 0x6)
Slightly fuller and around middle, Kelly blocks it out.
Overpitches it, around off, Nick Kelly leans on and drives it to the right of the bowler. Mohammad Wasim chases it down from mid off and cuts it off to restrict the batter for a couple of runs.
Nagging length, around off, Nick Kelly looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the front pad. The ball rolls away towards the point region.

A massive appeal for LBW by the bowler but is not given by the umpire! They aren't going for a review here! Naseem lands it full and around middle, swings it in, Nick Kelly misses his flick shot and gets hit on the front pad. Probably, going down leg.
Hard length, on top of off, Nick Kelly goes back and pats it down towards backward point.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, Kelly helps it on its way to deep fine leg for a single.
Swings it into the pads, on a full length, around leg, Kelly lunges and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Again a yorker, around off, Nick Kelly jams it out towards cover.
A yorker and well outside off, Rhys Mariu comes forward and opens bat face to slice it to wide deep third for a single.
WIDE! Sprays it down the leg side, slightly fuller, Rhys Mariu swings at it but misses. Called a wide.
Nagging length, around off, Rhys defends it to cover.

SIX! PUMPED! Rhys Mariu takes a full advantage of the free hit now! Javed bowls it on a dragged length and around off, Mariu shuffles across to cover the line and whacks it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Starts with a good-length ball, into the pads, Rhys Mariu drops it down into the pitch off the front foot. Oh... No, Akif Javed has overstepped and a Free-Hit is coming!
First run of the day! Back of a length and wide outside off, Rhys Mariu gets width to extend his arms as he slice it to wide deep third for a single to get off the mark.
BEATEN! Dragged length and outside off, seaming away, Rhys Mariu looks to drive it to the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Goes fuller now and touch outside off, Rhys Mariu leans on to drive it but gets it through the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket.
On a good length, around off, Rhys Mariu looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
BEAUTY! This is on that hard length and in the channel outside off, gets it to shape away after pitching. Rhys Mariu gets squared up as he looks to defend it and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Begins with an outswinger, on a back of a length and well outside off, moves away, Rhys Mariu watches it carefully and leaves it alone.
